text: Huaycán de Pariachi is an archaeological site in Peru. It is located in Huaycán, District of Ate, Lima. Retrieved August 20, 2023. Retrieved August 20, 2023. Retrieved August 20, 2023. Retrieved August 20, 2023. It was part of the Ichma culture and the Inca Empire. Retrieved August 20, 2023. Retrieved August 20, 2023. Retrieved August 20, 2023. Retrieved August 20, 2023. == Description == Before the Spanish conquest, Huaycán de Pariachi was one of the main administrative centers. The Incas Retrieved August 20, 2023.
